      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You have hit on a very common concern; in Toronto, escrow agents are licensed professionals under strict supervision by the Financial Services Authority, which holds them personally liable for any negligence or fraud. The funds are held in paralegally funded accounts (segregated at a client trust line), meaning they must be returned or applied per your contract, and acting as a guardian could lead to immediate legal prosecution and license revocation. Essentially, the system is designed so that the only way for these funds to disappear without your knowledge is for them to walk out of the industry entirely.",
